The paper deals with a multi-cell network and proposes a new precoding technique for massive MIMO systems. The paper discusses the use of pilot sequences and channel estimates, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference suppression and spatial transmission design, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed technique and compares it with other precoding techniques, which is a common practice in communication systems (cs.COM).
